</caption>
<paragraph pageId="73" pageNumber="74">
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia jaliscana" order="Myrtales" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="jaliscana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Conostegia jaliscana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a rare species reported usually from alongside streams. It has few-flowered inflorescences and relatively long and acute to acuminate floral buds. 
<bibRefCitation author="Schnell, CE" journalOrPublisher="Harvard University" pageId="243" pageNumber="244" refId="B77" refString="Schnell, CE, 1996. The Genus Conostegia (Melastomataceae). Harvard University" title="The Genus Conostegia (Melastomataceae)" year="1996">Schnell (1996)</bibRefCitation>
placed 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia jaliscana" order="Myrtales" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="jaliscana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Conostegia jaliscana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with the three Jamaican endemic in his section 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Myrtales" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Conostegia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Conostegia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but also hinted to the possibility of 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia jaliscana" order="Myrtales" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="jaliscana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Conostegia jaliscana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
being closely related to species in his subgenus 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="(Lobatostigma)" order="Myrtales" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Lobatostigma">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Lobatostigma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This latter hypothesis is the one supported in the molecular phylogeny.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
